.TH SHOREWALL-NFT-PROXYNDP 5 "2026-04-24" "shorewall-nft 1.10.2" "File Formats"
.SH NAME
shorewall\-nft\-proxyndp \- proxy NDP (IPv6 neighbour discovery proxy) for shorewall-nft
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.I proxyndp
file configures proxy NDP (Neighbour Discovery Protocol) entries for IPv6.
Each row causes the firewall to answer NDP Neighbour Solicitations on behalf
of the specified address on the named interface.

The format is identical to
.IR shorewall\-nft\-proxyarp (5)
but applies to IPv6 addresses.

.SH FILE FORMAT
Location:
.I /etc/shorewall/proxyndp
(or inside a merged
.IR /etc/shorewall46/ ).
.PP
Columns are whitespace-separated.  Lines beginning with
.B #
are comments.

.TS
l l l.
Column	Required	Description
_
ADDRESS	yes	IPv6 address to proxy-NDP for
INTERFACE	yes	Interface on which to answer NS messages
EXTERNAL	yes	External interface facing the requester
HAVEROUTE	no	Yes/No — whether a host route already exists
PERSISTENT	no	Yes/No — whether to survive firewall restarts
.TE

.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Proxy NDP for a DMZ IPv6 host:
.RS
.nf
#ADDRESS              INTERFACE  EXTERNAL
2001:db8::50          eth1       eth0
.fi
.RE

.SH SEE ALSO
.BR shorewall\-nft (8),
.BR shorewall\-nft\-proxyarp (5),
.BR shorewall\-nft\-interfaces (5)

